1775175408085315	command-lattice-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkyTOeZ5M5QAAAAAAQa61bvb1ugAAAAEvAw		item.create	bn-2fk0	{"description":"When merging a workspace into default, if default has uncommitted local edits to files the workspace also modified, the merge overwrites the local edits without warning. This causes repeated regressions when fixes are applied directly to default's working copy.\n\nExample: camera.rs was edited directly in default to fix pan speed and scroll zoom. A workspace (bn-1fj7) branched before those edits and touched camera.rs. On merge, the workspace version replaced default's edited version, reverting the fixes silently.\n\nExpected behavior: maw should either (1) warn about uncommitted local changes that would be overwritten, (2) refuse to merge until local changes are committed, or (3) treat local edits as a conflict requiring resolution.\n\nCurrent behavior: local-vs-merge conflicts ARE detected for some files, but the merge still proceeds and the local edits can be lost if the conflict resolution picks the wrong side, or if some files aren't flagged as conflicts.","kind":"bug","title":"Workspace merge silently overwrites uncommitted default edits without warning"}	blake3:abCYrjOZFfPzl23xi60TH8z_-TRJPWRuZi740_xnkz4
